    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "DTC Explanation: P0600"
    },
    {
      "type": "dtc",
      "code": "P0600",
      "text": "DTC P0600: ECU internal communication error"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Detection principle explanation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "2146_3.0_jpn_11231349_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If an abnormality occurs in the communication between the driver IC with the failure diagnosis function and the CPU, and the CPU is unable to acquire failure diagnosis information from each driver for a set period of time or longer, the PGM-FI ECU judges that a failure has occurred and stores the DTC."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Detection frequency, detection sequence, detection time required, detection method type, OBD status"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "rows": [
        [
          "D/C: Drive Cycle"
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Detection execution conditions"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "rows": [
        [
          "[ ]: HDS Parameters"
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Failure Criteria"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "No signal from each driver"
        },
        {
          "text": "Abnormal signals from each driver"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Estimated Failure Site"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "PGM-FI ECU internal circuit failure"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Store and clear DTC"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If the vehicle is determined to be faulty, the PGM-FI warning light comes on and the temporary DTC, DTC and freeze data are stored in the PGM-FI ECU memory."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If the vehicle is diagnosed and determined to be normal after running consecutive 3D/C runs, the PGM-FI warning light will turn off. In addition, the PGM-FI warning light, temporary DTC, DTC and freeze data are cleared by using the clear command of the scan tool (including HDS) or by removing the 12V battery terminal."
    }
  ],
